SCALE: 1/1%' = 1'-0"
FLOOR PLAN GENERAL NOTES

BOLLARDS ARE TO BE LOCATED WITHIN THE BUILDING TO PROTECT EXPOSED ELECTRICAL PANELS, ELECTRICAL GEAR, ROOF DRAIN PIPING, WATER LINES, GAS LINES, AND SPRINKLER TEST DRAIN PIPING WITHIN & OF WAREHOUSE FLOOR - PROVIDE REPLACEABLE YELLOW SLEEVE.
PROVIDE BARRIER RAILS TO PROTECT EXPOSED FIRE
JOOTUR GUARDS PROVIDE 2X2x48 HIGH STAINLESS STEEL CORNER QUARDS (TYP.) AT ALL EXPOSED CORNERS, ADHERE TO WALL (NO
.PROVIDE SEALANT WHERE EDGE OF TILE ABUTS GYPSUM. REFER TO DE [AIL 21 48 28 FOR TYPICAL METAL STUD OPENINGS AND CONTROL JOINT DETAILS. GC TO DETERMINE CONSTRUCTION METHODOLOGY.
REFER TO DE [AL 21 A11.1 FOR TYPICAL CHAIR RAIL DETAIL. 1. REFER TO SHEET A115 FOR FLOOR TRANSITION DETAILS 4A, 48, 4C, SA, 58, AND 5C.
SHEET NOTES
1 INSULATED HOLLOW METAL SERVICE DOOR AND FRAME. PAINT SEMI-OLOSS. GROUT FRAME SOLID AT CONCRETE OPENINGS. PAINT INTERIOR SIDE SAFETY RED PT-7.
2 INSULATED MANUAL OVERHEAD SECTIONAL DOCK DOOR & DOCK LEVELER EQUIPMENT, WHERE SCHEDULED.
3 LINE OF PID PLATFORM ABOVE.
4 PID PLATFORM STAIR
6º DIA, CONCRETE-FILLED GALVANIZED STEEL BOLLARDS. PROVIDE REPLACEABLE YELLOW SLEEVE (TYP.) (SEE DETAILS ON SHEET A7.2)
6 INSULATED MOTORIZED OVERHEAD SECTIONAL DOOR. SEE DOOR AND FRAME SCHEDULE.
8 6' DIA X 10-0" LONG CONCRETE-FILLED GALVANIZED STEEL BOLLABOR AT GENERATOR AND TRANSFORMERS PROVIDE REPLACEABLE YELLOW SLEEVE. (TYP.) SEE 4D/5D 17.2 FOR DETAILS
9 ROOF LADDER WITH ROOF HATCH ABOVE - SEE ADE FOR DETAILS

10 HOSE VALVE CONNECTION - MAINTAIN 12" CLEARANCE AT LATCH SIDE OF DOORS - REFER TO FIRE PROTECTION DRAWINGS 11 FIRE RISER LOCATION - MAINTAIN 12" CLEARANCE AT LATCH SIDE OF DOORS - SEE DETAIL 2E149.6 - REFER TO FIRE PROTECTION DRAWINGS
12 ROOF DRAIN AND OVERFLOW DRAIN, CENTER BETWEEN OPENINGS. EXTEND OVER FLOW DRAIN THROUGH PRE-CAST. PROVIDE LAMBS TONGUE
13 PROVIDE 15MIL VAPOR RETARDER UNDER ALL SLABS ON OROUND

14 INTERIOR COLUMN - SHALL BE PAINTED SAFETY YELLOW UP TO 12 A.F.F. AND NO PAINT SHALL BE APPLIED FROM 12' A.F.F. TO UNDERSIDE OF ROOF OR MEZZANINE STRUCTURE. ON COLUMNS WITH FIRE EXTINGUISHERS, PAINT 24" LOING SAFETY RED BAND, ALL 4 SIDES OF COLUMN, AT A.F. F. PAINT ENTIRE COLUMN SAFETY RED WHERE FIRE HOSE CONNECTIONS ARE LOCATED. REFER TO SHEET 14 M0
19 HOSE BIB - REFER TO PLUMBING DRAWINGS. PROVIDE FROST PROOF SILLCOCK AT EXTERIOR WALLS. ENSURE ALL PIPING IS WITHIN THE THERMAL ENVELOPE PRE-ENGINEERED EXT. BREAK ROOM
WIRE MESH PARTITION TO GO UP TO WITHIN AN INCH OR TWO OF THE BOTTOM OF THE CANOPY. INSTALL PER MANUFACTURER'S RECOMMENDATIONS.
3 KNOX BOX MOUNTED & ABOVE FINISHED FLOOR COMPACTOR. CONTRACTOR TO COORDINATION WALL OPENING WITH OWNER. PROVIDE DOCK BUMPERS AT COMPACTOR.
25 VRC - REFER TO ELECTRICAL FOR POWER REQUIREMENTS
MOF SDEN -REFER TO ELECTRICAL DRAWINGS STEEL BARRIER, REFER TO FIRE RISER BARRIERS 26/0 6. AVOIDONATE CLEARANCE WITH ELECTRICAL
HOUTENTONERONRENDERING PAD - REFER TO STRUCTURAL DETAIL 984.5. COORDINATE WITH PANEL PROVIDER. AUGER. CONTRACTOR TO COORDINATE WALL OPENING WITH OWNER
32 DOWNSPOUT

EMERGENCY SHOWER -REFER TO PLUMBING REMOTE HOSE VALVE CONVECTION AT INTERIOR COLUMN - COORDINATE WITH ONENTENANI FOR FINAL LOCATIONA SABEAACHENASERSTED BOLLER LARETE SURFACE MOUNTED STEEL BOLLARD. LOCATE SUCH THAT ANCHORS ARE MIN 3' FROM ALL CONCRETE JOINTS - SEE DETAIL 4AA11.1
